<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: HEART GROUP OFFERS QUAKE SURVIVAL KITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PATRICK McCARTNEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Seeing a need to fill after the Jan. 17 earthquake caught so many residents by 
surprise, the Ventura County chapter of the American Heart Assn. is selling 
three-day survival emergency kits to help raise funds. 
</P>
<P>
 Proceeds from sales of the Ark III and Survival Basics kits will go toward 
fighting heart disease and stroke, association officials say. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ark III, which costs $14, contains an emergency blanket, three days of 
food for one person and six packets of water. The Survival Basics, available 
for $21, contains a flashlight, batteries and medical kit in addition to the 
contents of the Ark III and six more packets of water. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the association at 485-4300. PATRICK McCARTNEY 
</P>
