</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 7-year-old Ventura girl died Friday after being struck by a delivery van 
while riding her bicycle, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred at 1:30 p.m. in the 300 block of West Simpson Street, 
just down the street from Sheridan Way School. 
</P>
<P>
 Karina J. Arias was pronounced dead 40 minutes later in the emergency room of 
the Ventura County Medical Center, said Deputy Coroner Mitch Breese. 
</P>
<P>
 According to residents and police, the girl had been riding her bicycle when 
she veered into the street and collided with a delivery van driven by Sukhvir 
Singh Grewal, 32, of Santa Paula. 
</P>
<P>
 Paramedics, who felt a faint pulse at the scene, took the girl to the 
hospital, but doctors could not revive her. Breese said Karina suffered a major 
head injury. 
</P>
<P>
 Police Cpl. Ray Broomfield said it did not appear that Grewal had been 
speeding. Hours after the accident, part of Simpson Street remained blocked off 
as police conducted their investigation. 
</P>
<P>
 Neighbors said Karina had been staying with her aunt, who recently moved to 
Simpson Street. The girl's parents, Raul and Rosa Arias, live on Sherwin Avenue 
in Ventura. JULIE FIELDS 
