<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; HEAD-ON CRASH INTO TREE KILLS MOTORIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 26-year-old Oxnard man died Friday morning when his car smashed head-on into 
a eucalyptus tree on the Pacific Coast Highway, according to the California 
Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
 John A. Montoya died of head injuries after his 1993 Nissan plowed into a tree 
in the road's median at 9:30 a.m., according to CHP officers. He was traveling 
north on the highway, just beyond the Nauman Road exit, they said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers did not know how fast Montoya was driving or why his car hit the 
tree. 
</P>
<P>
 He was wearing a seat belt but died from the force of the impact, they said. 
CONSTANCE SOMMER 
