<HEADLINE>
<P>
HEALTH CARE REFORM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * The Times editorial of March 17 on health care reform was right on 
target.Certainly President Clinton needs to vigorously sell health care reform. 
However, as citizens we need to help. 
</P>
<P>
 We can do this by first educating ourselves on the issues and then speaking 
out clearly on the changes we want to our legislators whether by letter, 
telephone, fax or in person. It is imperative that we take the responsibility 
for communicating our ideas to those who represent us. And let us not wait for 
the "other guy" to do it! 
</P>
<P>
 Health care reform is so important it cannot and must not be a "Big Flop." 
Speak out now.  
</P>
<P>
 EVELYN L. HINTZE 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 
</P>
