AMERICAN SAVINGS SELLS CREDIT-CARD PORTFOLIO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 American Savings Bank said Friday that it has sold its $140-million 
credit-card portfolio to GE Capital Consumer Card Co. 
</P>
<P>
 The bank was one of the few savings institutions that still maintained its own 
credit-card business. Great Western Bank and Home Savings of America also 
recently sold their portfolios. 
</P>
