<P>
 Woolworth Suppliers Told to Wait: Several retail credit and factoring 
companies have told suppliers to hold off on shipments to Woolworth Corp. until 
the retailer provides more information about an internal investigation into 
alleged accounting irregularities.Factoring companies guarantee manufacturers 
will be paid for shipments to retailers. Retail credit companies advise 
factoring companies and suppliers about the credit worthiness of retailers. The 
companies said they are concerned that a pending restatement of Woolworth's 
past earnings could adversely affect the company's ability to pay suppliers. 
The New York-based operator of specialty and general merchandise store chains 
said Wednesday it will restate figures for its last fiscal year, which ended 
Jan. 29. 
