 GTE California Seeks OK for Rate Reduction: The GTE Corp. unit submitted its 
annual shareable earnings filing with the California Public Utilities 
Commission, asking it to approve a $7.7-million revenue and rate reduction.The 
Thousand Oaks-based company said that if approved, the refunds would be passed 
along as a 3.35% credit on customers' bills for local and toll services. The 
reduction would amount to a saving of about $1 monthly for residential 
customers, GTE said. The refunds, reflecting GTE's 1993 earnings, would be made 
in August and September. GTE California provides local voice, data and video 
services and regional toll calling for more than 3.1 million customers. 
