<HEADLINE>
<P>
NORTHRIDGE ROLLS PAST UCSD, STRETCHES VOLLEYBALL STREAK TO 4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Peter Piexoto had 14 kills and Oliver Heitmann added seven as Cal State 
Northridge defeated UC San Diego, 15-5, 15-8, 15-3, in a Mountain Pacific 
Sports Federation men's volleyball match Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory was the fourth in a row for the Matadors (14-8, 10-6 in conference 
play) and their sixth in the last seven matches. 
</P>
<P>
 Piexoto, a junior outside hitter from Soquel High near Santa Cruz, had a .571 
hitting percentage, with Heitmann at .636 and Jason Hughes (six kills) at .556. 
Northridge hit .366 as a team, including a .393 mark in the final game. 
</P>
<P>
 Collin Smith, who had five kills, led the Matadors with nine digs and four 
blocks. 
</P>
<P>
 Tyson Kerr had 10 kills for UC San Diego (2-19, 0-15). 
</P>
