<P>
POLL PUTS BRITONS AMONG WORLD'S GLOOMIEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Britons are among the world's most dissatisfied, distrustful and pessimistic 
people, a poll conducted in Britain, Germany, Japan and the United States 
reported today.  
</P>
<P>
 Results of the poll of more than 5,500 people interviewed about their view of 
the world between March 5 and 11 were published simultaneously in Britain's 
Guardian newspaper, Germany's Der Spiegel, Japan's Asahi Shimbun and the New 
York Times. 
</P>
<P>
 The poll found 85% of Britons were dissatisfied with the general situation of 
the world, compared to 82% of Germans, 67% of Americans and 66% of Japanese, 
the Guardian said. 
</P>
<P>
 Only 13% of British people were optimistic that things would improve in the 
next five years, against 16% of Japanese, 18% of Germans and 19% of Americans. 
</P>
