<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; 13 PEOPLE ARRESTED IN RAID AT COASTAL INN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police arrested 13 people this week in a raid at a local motel, taking them 
into custody over suspected drug, weapons and warrant violations. 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa Police Sgt. Matt Collett said a monthlong investigation of the 
Coastal Inn was initiated because of complaints from residents about the motel 
at 2374 Newport Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 Collett said 23 officers took part in the Wednesday evening raid, circling the 
motel about 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 A part-time manager at the motel said Friday said she was not allowed to talk 
about the arrests. 
</P>
<P>
 The district attorney's office on Friday charged Laura Arredondo, 32, of Costa 
Mesa and Terri Rauch, 44, of Costa Mesa with the alleged sale of narcotics. 
</P>
<P>
 Charges have not yet been filed against the other people arrested. 
</P>
<P>
 Randy Lee Howe, 36, of Costa Mesa was arrested on suspicion of possession of 
illegal needles. Miles Crossen, 38, of Costa Mesa was arrested on suspicion of 
possession of a sawed-off shotgun. 
</P>
<P>
 Catherine Herbert, 31, of Huntington Beach and Sandra Christensen, 45, of 
Costa Mesa was arrested on suspicion of possession of narcotics. 
</P>
<P>
 Arrested on outstanding warrants were Shelli Firsich, 32, of Santa Ana and 
Matthew Depiano, 40, Gary Hall, 40, James Cobb, 25, James Zugay, 44, Joan 
Cooper, 33, and Kimberly Fergus, 28, all of Costa Mesa.WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
