<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAKE FOREST; QUAKE PREPAREDNESS TIPS TO BE PRESENTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Orange County Fire Department is offering tips on how to prepare for a 
major earthquake at a community meeting to be held here April 18. 
</P>
<P>
 Called "Are You Ready For The Big One?" the informational session will start 
at 7 p.m. in a multiuse tent at the Saddleback Valley Community Church at 1 
Saddleback Parkway, located near the intersection of El Toro Road and Santa 
Margarita Parkway. 
</P>
<P>
 Battalion Chief Don Forsyth will lead the free program, presenting a slide 
show and explaining how people can prepare for an earthquake in the Saddleback 
Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is sponsored by the Fire Department and the Saddleback Valley 
Community Church. For more information, call (714) 581-9100, Ext. 118. 
</P>
</TEXT>
