<HEADLINE>
<P>
5 MEMBERS OF GANG HELD IN FATAL STABBING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG HERNANDEZ, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Five members of a Placentia gang have been arrested in connection with the 
fatal stabbing of a Fullerton gang member during a brawl Thursday afternoon, 
police said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Ricky Michaels, 18, of Placentia was stabbed several times in the chest during 
the fight which broke out about 4:45 p.m. in the courtyard of an apartment 
complex in the 3100 block of Pearl Drive, said Sgt. Danny Becerra. 
</P>
<P>
 Arrested at their homes in Placentia late Thursday night and Friday afternoon 
were: Rene Ramon Castro, 26, Johnny Richard Martinez, 18, Jose Luis Villanueva, 
19, Trinidad Villanueva, 24, and a 17-year-old male. 
</P>
<P>
 The adults were arrested without incident and taken to Fullerton city jail. 
The 17-year-old was taken to Orange County Juvenile Hall. All are being held on 
suspicion of murder. 
</P>
<P>
 Words had been exchanged between the two gangs at the apartment complex 
earlier in the day, police said. The Placentia gang left but returned and began 
a fistfight a short time later. Three people were stabbed during the fight. 
</P>
<P>
 Michaels died about 45 minutes after being taken to the hospital. Charles 
Ernest Matthews, 20, of Placentia and a 17-year-old male from Anaheim were 
stabbed in the torso, but their injuries are not life-threatening. All are 
admitted gang members, Becerra said. 
</P>
<P>
 "These particular street gangs have not demonstrated hostility toward each 
other in the past," Becerra said. "They all seemed to get along because they 
live in the same area."MURDERS 
</P>
</TEXT>
