WEST VALLEY FOCUS: SYLMAR; BRIDGE RETROFITTING TO BEGIN IN JUNE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHIP JOHNSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Caltrans officials announced that bridge retrofitting work in Encino will 
begin in early June. 
</P>
<P>
 Five bridges, including a pedestrian crossing at Encino Avenue, will be 
retrofitted as part of a statewide retrofit program that began in 1989, said 
Russell Snyder, a Caltrans spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
 Construction work will begin in early June and is expected to continue for 
about one year, he said. The cost of the retrofit program is $287,000, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Most of the work is expected to be done at night and during off hours, but 
Snyder warned that lane closures may be necessary from time to time during 
construction. All lane closures will be announced beforehand by the agency, he 
said. CHIP JOHNSON 
</P>
